%h1
  Your mind: a user's guide

%p
  %b
    Mindapples is on a mission to teach everyone in the UK how their minds work.
    
%p
  %i 
    Your Mind: A User's Guide
  is an education programme from Mindapples that teaches practical insights from neuroscience & psychology to help people maintain their minds and use them more effectively. Delivered in bite-sized 60-minute chunks for busy people, and backed-up with beautifully-designed learning resources, this is a fresh, empowering approach to mental wellbeing and performance that helps people work smarter, talk more openly about their minds, and stay healthy and resilient in a high-pressure environments.
  
%p
  The programme covers all the essential topics people need to understand to function well in the modern world. The full ten-module programme covers:
  %ul
    %li Love your mind: an introduction to maintaining your mind and staying mentally well
    %li Master your moods: managing moods and emotions and staying psychologically resilient
    %li Get motivated: the key ingredients that make some tasks easier and more energising than others
    %li Handle pressure: spotting the signs of stress and using your resources to turn pressure into challenge
    %li Know yourself: introducing the science of personality to understand your strengths and weaknesses
    %li Train your mind: how intelligence and learning works, and techniques for improving your mind and building new habits
    %li Make smarter decisions: how we really make decisions, and how to apply your mind effectively to daily challenges
    %li Influence people: the hidden ways in which we influence each other, and how to use your own influence positively
    %li Work collaboratively: communication and language, group dynamics and how to work smoothly and productively with others
    %li Think creatively: how our minds really come up with new ideas, and simple techniques to keep your mind fresh and creative
 
%p
  All our programme content is rigorously researched and based on the latest findings from experimental psychology and neuroscience and delivered by experienced trainers. Our sessions get amazing feedback, with 
  %i
    over 90% of participants rating our sessions as "good" or "excellent" 
  and the same number saying they will change their behaviour as a result of these sessions. 
  
%p
  %i
    "I certainly found the approach novel and informative which is praise indeed having been to so many "stress management sessions"."
  %br
  %b
    Dr David Matthews, MB, BS, DRCOG, DOccMed, AFOM, FRCGP, Occupational Physician

